text: Wilbert Carl "Webb" Schultz (January 31, 1898 – July 26, 1986) was a Major League Baseball pitcher. Schultz played for the Chicago White Sox in . In 1 career game, he had a 0–0 record, going one inning, and giving up one run and one hit. He batted and threw left-handed.
